<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[227,1436,1547,1758]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
This species is recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[593,703,1591,1617]" name="Morocco" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Morocco</collectingCountry>
. Its 
<typeStatus box="[756,809,1591,1617]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">type</typeStatus>
, however, is lost so we couldn’t examine it. Only a few characterisics could be extracted from the literature: body surface polished; ocelli small; pronotum as long as mesonotum; mesonotum sparsely punctate; propodeum as long as mesonotum, gibbous, polished, with central depression narrow, sublateral carina absent, posterior spine present and very short; wings micropterous; metasoma strongly arched and with tergites coriaceous.
</paragraph>
